text: Korak is town and Union Council of Awaran District in the Balochistan province of Pakistan. It is at 26°50'38N 65°44'3E and is 648 metres (2129 feet) above sea level. During the floods of 2007, 137 households (619 people) here were affected. Category:Tehsils of Balochistan Category:Awaran District
title: Korak, Pakistan
